WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Roman_Wheel' is a Workbench game where the game board is in the
form of a wheel containing 8 positions that surround a central
position, that central position is linked to 4 of the positions in
the wheel. You have to place the numbers from 1 to 8 in the wheel
and they must be put clockwise.

  Try to place all the numbers in the right order, in the minimum
of moves possible.

  Have fun!

FEATURES
--------

-Simple installation: just run the game and play!

-Small package, the Lha archive is smaller than 50K, so it
 doesn't take ages to download :)

-The game plays on the Workbench screen and its window is
 resizeable.

